            "id": "d4f83a1a60d94f66a296a",
            "questionText": "During an earthquake, the Earth's crust generates various types of seismic waves. A seismological station detects the P-wave $!$35$!$ seconds before the S-wave. The P-wave travels at $!$6.0\\ \\text{km/s}$!$ and the S-wave at $!$3.5\\ \\text{km/s}$!$. If the earthquake generates P-waves with a wavelength of $!$12.0\\ \\text{km}$!$, calculate the wavelength of the S-waves when they reach the station.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "7110c120eef4455997959",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct wave equation that relates wave speed, frequency, and wavelength. Which of the following formulas is the correct one?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "e2484863-f982-4229-94d2-b6df0b9b92ca",
                        "1e88a9b9-7a2e-4e44-b95a-bcdedbb9da85",
                        "91d66318-1623-4c88-b48c-56e3cfc2c189",
                        "c76dc2d1-7988-4901-a0e0-fda851b381a7"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = f\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$f = \\frac{\\lambda}{v}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = v \\cdot f^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "050efb005ac34ca19e697",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, using the formula from the previous step for the P-waves, calculate the frequency. Use the P-wave speed $!$6.0\\ \\text{km/s}$!$ and wavelength $!$12.0\\ \\text{km}$!$ in the relation $!$v = f\\lambda$!$. What is the frequency?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.5"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Hz",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "e2484863-f982-4229-94d2-b6df0b9b92ca",
                        "91d66318-1623-4c88-b48c-56e3cfc2c189",
                        "1e88a9b9-7a2e-4e44-b95a-bcdedbb9da85"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "70bf983f7a19467785724",
                    "stepText": "Now that we have the frequency, let's determine the wavelength of the S-waves when they reach the station. Using the S-wave speed $!$3.5\\ \\text{km/s}$!$ and the same frequency, apply the wave equation. What is the wavelength of the S-waves?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "7.0"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "km",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "e2484863-f982-4229-94d2-b6df0b9b92ca",
                        "c76dc2d1-7988-4901-a0e0-fda851b381a7",
                        "91d66318-1623-4c88-b48c-56e3cfc2c189"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "674d05ce80e040d99f705",
                    "stepText": "Finally, consider the fact that the P-wave arrives 35 seconds before the S-wave. What does this time difference indicate about the waves generated from the same earthquake?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
