        {
            "id": "8e1cc605ca8148e19bd9a",
            "questionText": "An incident sound wave with an amplitude of $!$0.8\\,\\text{Pa}$!$ strikes a wall with acoustic panels that absorb $!$75\\%$!$ of its energy. Assuming the intensity of a sound wave is proportional to the square of its amplitude ($!$I \\propto A^2$!$), calculate the amplitude of the sound wave that is reflected from the wall.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "8d99ab38149a4ef7bd7e2",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the relationship between the intensity of a sound wave and its amplitude. Please select the correct formula that represents this relationship.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "e2484863-f982-4229-94d2-b6df0b9b92ca",
                        "1e88a9b9-7a2e-4e44-b95a-bcdedbb9da85",
                        "91d66318-1623-4c88-b48c-56e3cfc2c189"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I \\propto A^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I \\propto A$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I \\propto A^3$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "31e522b1cbe44c528603f",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now consider that the wall absorbs 75% of the incident energy. What fraction of the original energy is reflected? Please choose the correct factor.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$0.25$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$0.75$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$0.5$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "45f7102c95124bc2b556e",
                    "stepText": "Now, using the proportional relationship $!$I \\propto A^2$!$, set up an equation that relates the square of the reflected amplitude to the square of the initial amplitude multiplied by the reflected energy fraction. Choose the correctly set up equation.",
